
** Oracle Clusterware

*** Shared Files

  - voting disk
  - oracle cluster registry (ocr)

*** Storage

  - iSCSI (yes)
  - NAS (no), except NETAPP if it presents as iSCSI

*** Processes

  - css (cluster synchronization service)
    - interfaces with thirdparty clusterware
  - crs (cluster ready service)
    - reads the configuration from the oracle cluster registry
  - evm (event management)
  - ons (oracle notification service)
  - oprocd (process monitor daemon, fencing service)

  - The processes, (r) indicates is startet by root:

    oprocd (r)
    racgmain
    racgimon
    ons
    evmd (r)
    evmd.bin
    evmlogger
    crsd.bin (r)
    init.cssd (r),
    ocssd (r)
    ocssd.bin

*** rconfig

  - can convert single instance
  - has too a "verify only" mode 
  - works not with pure raw devices

*** Compatipility

  - 11g Clusterware can work with 10g ASM and Database

